    {
      "id": "220d63352c275a6e2edbf5ea43031fb9dab8804d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2013-01-30 22:35:27.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 6:\n\nI think this patch itself is pretty good.\n\nI now think that actually removing imports from pinger list is a good idea, but fine to add it as a separate patch as a refinement.\nThe few ms logic is kind of hard to justify, few ms here and there and suddenly we have huge jitter problem which is very bad for large scale nodes. There was even a discussion of disconnecting from servers if there is no outstanding state for them on a client, and so this removal patch might be the first step in that direction.\n\nThe connect flag or state is a great idea too, I think. It's just server that knows if there's external health network, so it's in great position to allow or disallow pinging. Another benefit is by making it server controlled there's less need to ensure all module parameters are synchronized, and instead the server will just dictate to the clients (new enough, anyway) what to do. It's fine to have this as a separate patch too.\nAnd I was also thinking that perhaps we can revive a bit of pinging logic on the server for when we know thee are uncommitted transactions and the client is expected to ping us soon. To take it a step further, perhaps we can have \"level 2 pinger disabling\" where the clients would ping when they have some outstanding state for the servers (like waiting for something to commit, or holding locks) which would be usable to reduce pinger overhead even in the face of no health network present (this add on might be a yet another patch on top of a more simple one, but depends on how hard is it to do I guess).",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 6
    },
    {
      "id": "f391291123f69086ca4235f555d9d7586457a04d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 284,
        "name": "Emoly Liu",
        "email": "emoly@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "liuying_emoly"
      },
      "date": "2013-01-31 02:42:22.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 6: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\nAfter discussion with liwei, I think this patch is good for me. \n\nI prefer not to remove imports from the list, but probably there are some unforeseen problems in a large-scale system. As for how to set this parameter, I think we could find a better way to do it between server and client pair, instead of module parameter. But now I have no idea.\n\nWhat's more, we can add a test for this feature in the future.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 6
    },
